olive oil
½ lemon
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 Couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 tsp honey
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet chicken breast

• Preheat BBQ to high heat. Boil the kettle.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• Zest lemon to get a pinch and slice in half.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt and lemon zest. Season to taste.

• In a medium bowl, add couscous and chicken-style stock powder.
• Add the boiling water (see ingredients) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with plate and leave for 5 minutes.
• Fluff up with fork and set aside.

• Spread peeled pumpkin wedges over a large microwave-safe plate. Cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave pumpkin on high, 5 minutes.
• Drain any excess liquid. Brush both sides with oil and season with salt and pepper.
• When BBQ is hot, grill pumpkin on flat plate until browned and tender, 4-5 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate, drizzle over the honey and set aside.

No BBQ? Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Place pumpkin peeled wedges on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• Grill chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Grill mild chorizo until charred and cooked through, 4-6 minutes either side.
• Grill lemon, cut side down, until charred, 2-3 minutes.

No BBQ? In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Roughly chop mild chorizo. Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chorizo until golden, 8 minutes.
No BBQ? Heat a large frying pan over high heat and cook lemon, cut side down, until charred, 1-2 minutes.

• Roughly chop chorizo and chicken.
• To the bowl with the couscous, add chorizo, baby spinach leaves, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide grilled chorizo and chicken couscous between bowls.
• Top with pumpkin wedges. Drizzle over lemon yoghurt and tear over parsley. Enjoy!